10:01.851 --> 10:05.522
We are currently in the middle

10:01.851 --> 10:05.522
of a process called discovery.

10:05.522 --> 10:07.482
What is discovery,

10:05.522 --> 10:07.482
you might ask?

10:07.482 --> 10:09.984
It's one of the most important

10:07.482 --> 10:09.984
parts of any case,

10:09.984 --> 10:11.652
because it's when both parties

10:11.652 --> 10:13.530
are able to discover,

10:11.652 --> 10:13.530
if you will,

10:13.530 --> 10:17.576
information that is relevant

10:13.530 --> 10:17.576
to the claims at issue.

10:17.576 --> 10:20.495
Now this brings us to

10:17.576 --> 10:20.495
another key term, "relevance."

10:20.495 --> 10:22.956
If a document or a piece

10:20.495 --> 10:22.956
of evidence is relevant,

10:22.956 --> 10:25.500
that means it has a tendency

10:22.956 --> 10:25.500
to prove or disprove

10:25.500 --> 10:26.960
an element in the case.

10:26.960 --> 10:30.671
This whole thing

10:26.960 --> 10:30.671
is just taking so darn long.

10:30.671 --> 10:33.174
Unfortunately, high-stakes

10:30.671 --> 10:33.174
class actions like these

10:33.174 --> 10:34.926
often move

10:33.174 --> 10:34.926
on a protracted timeline.

10:34.926 --> 10:36.511
WOMAN:

10:34.926 --> 10:36.511
Well, okay.

10:36.511 --> 10:39.306
But some of us don't have

10:36.511 --> 10:39.306
"a protracted timeline,"

10:39.306 --> 10:41.224
if you know what I mean.

10:41.224 --> 10:44.603
My son thinks

10:41.224 --> 10:44.603
I should get my own lawyer.

10:44.603 --> 10:46.396
You have every right

10:44.603 --> 10:46.396
to pursue

10:46.396 --> 10:48.315
independent

10:46.396 --> 10:48.315
legal representation.

10:48.315 --> 10:50.108
Having said that--

10:48.315 --> 10:50.108
Absolutely.

10:50.108 --> 10:53.570
Great to see the next generation

10:50.108 --> 10:53.570
stepping up, isn't it?

10:53.570 --> 10:55.029
Thank you, Ms. Brill.

10:56.364 --> 10:57.574
Hi, everyone.

10:57.574 --> 10:59.326
I'm so glad to be

10:57.574 --> 10:59.326
with you today.

10:59.326 --> 11:01.244
For those of you

10:59.326 --> 11:01.244
who don't know me yet,

11:01.244 --> 11:03.163
I'm your lead attorney,

11:01.244 --> 11:03.163
Howard Hamlin.

11:03.163 --> 11:05.123
Just call me Howard.

11:05.123 --> 11:08.709
And this is my co-counsel,

11:05.123 --> 11:08.709
Cliff Main.

11:08.709 --> 11:10.295
Listen.

11:10.295 --> 11:12.713
I know you all wanna get

11:10.295 --> 11:12.713
to the finish line.

11:12.713 --> 11:14.299
Boy, I sure do.

11:14.299 --> 11:16.134
But I'm gonna level with you.

11:16.134 --> 11:18.136
Truth is, we still have

11:16.134 --> 11:18.136
a ways to go.

11:19.095 --> 11:20.514
Why?

11:20.514 --> 11:24.058
Because we want

11:20.514 --> 11:24.058
the maximum from Sandpiper.

11:24.058 --> 11:27.061
We're pushing to get

11:24.058 --> 11:27.061
an extra 30 percent

11:27.061 --> 11:28.647
on top of the penalty.

11:28.647 --> 11:31.107
Not because we're greedy, no.

11:31.107 --> 11:33.276
Because it's what you deserve.

11:34.611 --> 11:36.363
Now, to get your due,

11:36.363 --> 11:39.199
it may take

11:36.363 --> 11:39.199
a little extra time.

11:39.199 --> 11:40.950
Is it worth it?

11:40.950 --> 11:42.035
I think it is.

11:43.578 --> 11:45.539
Because this isn't just

11:43.578 --> 11:45.539
about money.

11:47.541 --> 11:48.667
It's about people.

11:50.877 --> 11:53.547
It's about you. Sally, right?

11:53.547 --> 11:54.797
[CHUCKLES]

11:54.797 --> 11:56.299
Right. Sally.

11:56.924 --> 11:58.009
And you, sir.

11:59.302 --> 12:01.179
We're sending a message.

12:01.179 --> 12:02.889
We're not gonna let

12:01.179 --> 12:02.889
big corporations

12:02.889 --> 12:05.141
pick the pockets

12:02.889 --> 12:05.141
of hardworking folks.

12:05.141 --> 12:06.809
I wanna live in a world

12:06.809 --> 12:08.769
where people

12:06.809 --> 12:08.769
can trust each other.

12:10.104 --> 12:11.481
And I bet you do too.

12:13.441 --> 12:15.527
CLIFF: Thanks again, both of

12:13.441 --> 12:15.527
you.

12:13.441 --> 12:15.527
Thank you.

12:15.527 --> 12:16.735
Thank you for coming.

12:18.112 --> 12:19.239
Thank you.

12:19.239 --> 12:21.408
Oh, I feel better.

12:19.239 --> 12:21.408
Thank you.

12:22.701 --> 12:24.160
Goodbye.

12:22.701 --> 12:24.160
Okay.

12:24.160 --> 12:26.580
Bye now. You take care.

12:24.160 --> 12:26.580
Thank you.

12:29.416 --> 12:32.293
Well, I think we just

12:29.416 --> 12:32.293
put out a major fire.

12:32.293 --> 12:33.712
That was impressive.

12:33.712 --> 12:36.005
Erin, I'll see you

12:33.712 --> 12:36.005
back at the office.

12:33.712 --> 12:36.005
Okay.

12:36.005 --> 12:37.006
Bye, Howard.

12:37.006 --> 12:38.841
Howard, I need a minute.

12:41.052 --> 12:42.429
What's up?

12:42.429 --> 12:44.431
I threw a woman

12:42.429 --> 12:44.431
out of my car,

12:45.557 --> 12:47.642
in the middle of the street?

12:47.642 --> 12:50.604
And I zip,

12:47.642 --> 12:50.604
I just drive right past.

12:50.604 --> 12:52.480
That's what you're saying?

12:52.480 --> 12:53.732
I don't even--

12:55.358 --> 12:57.277
I don't know

12:55.358 --> 12:57.277
how to respond to that.

12:57.277 --> 12:58.861
I'm not asking you to respond.

12:58.861 --> 13:00.905
I just need you to know

12:58.861 --> 13:00.905
that I know.

13:00.905 --> 13:02.532
It wasn't me, Cliff.

13:00.905 --> 13:02.532
Whoever you think--

13:02.532 --> 13:04.992
Yeah, that's the kind of thing

13:02.532 --> 13:04.992
my son used to say.

13:04.992 --> 13:07.161
It was your Jaguar,

13:04.992 --> 13:07.161
your "Namaste" plate.

13:07.161 --> 13:08.996
It was you.

13:08.996 --> 13:11.874
Howard, there's no harm

13:08.996 --> 13:11.874
in asking for help.

13:11.874 --> 13:14.586
You got a lot of people

13:11.874 --> 13:14.586
in your corner.

13:14.586 --> 13:16.963
So there's the baggie

13:14.586 --> 13:16.963
at the country club.

13:16.963 --> 13:18.632
Yes.

13:16.963 --> 13:18.632
After that,

13:18.632 --> 13:21.092
some clients, who you can't name

13:18.632 --> 13:21.092
because of privilege,

13:21.092 --> 13:22.552
make insinuations.

13:22.552 --> 13:25.096
Then on Thursday,

13:22.552 --> 13:25.096
you have a business meeting,

13:25.096 --> 13:27.682
and you witness

13:25.096 --> 13:27.682
a Jaguar speeding past.

13:29.976 --> 13:31.561
Who were you meeting with?

13:31.561 --> 13:35.440
Not sure why that's germane,

13:31.561 --> 13:35.440
but Kim Wexler.

13:35.440 --> 13:37.358
She came to me

13:35.440 --> 13:37.358
for career advice.

13:42.781 --> 13:43.864
All right.

13:48.035 --> 13:49.078
Okay.

13:50.829 --> 13:51.872
Of course.

13:52.540 --> 13:53.625
Of course.

13:57.712 --> 14:00.507
Cliff, I know

13:57.712 --> 14:00.507
this wasn't easy for you.

14:00.507 --> 14:02.467
You came to me as a friend.

14:02.467 --> 14:03.760
I appreciate it.

14:03.760 --> 14:06.262
You can start today, Howard.

14:03.760 --> 14:06.262
Oh, I will.

14:06.262 --> 14:10.057
Because you're right,

14:06.262 --> 14:10.057
I do have a problem.

14:10.057 --> 14:12.059
Just not

14:10.057 --> 14:12.059
the problem you think.

14:12.059 --> 14:13.728
I have

14:12.059 --> 14:13.728
a Jimmy McGill problem.

14:13.728 --> 14:15.814
Jimmy McGill? Howard!

14:13.728 --> 14:15.814
Excuse me.

14:15.814 --> 14:16.897
Julie.

14:16.897 --> 14:18.692
[JAGUAR CHIRPS]

14:16.897 --> 14:18.692
Cancel my week.

14:19.776 --> 14:21.944
Yes. My whole week.

14:23.404 --> 14:24.947
Howard!

14:23.404 --> 14:24.947
[CAR MOTOR STARTING]

14:42.256 --> 14:45.426
[POP SONG PLAYING INDISTINCTLY

14:42.256 --> 14:45.426
ON CAR RADIO]

14:49.723 --> 14:51.432
